{
  "text": "Here Y \u00b5\u03c1\u03bd\u03c3 is antisymmetric in \u00b5\u03c1 and \u03bd\u03c3 and symmetric under \u00b5\u03c1 \u2194 \u03bd\u03c3; such an operator can be constructed in terms of L \u00b5\u03bd [CITATION_1] . Thus T \u2032 \u00b5\u03bd is physically equivalent to T \u00b5\u03bd , and the condition (1.4) makes conformal symmetry manifest.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "122981363"
