  "bib_entries": {
    "122981363": {
      "title": "Scale And Conformal Invariance In Quantum Field Theory",
      "abstract": "Abstract We study the relation between invariance under rigid and local changes of length scale. In two dimensions, we complete an argument of Zamolodchikov showing that the rigid invariance implies the local under broad conditions. In three or more dimensions we are unable to find either a general proof or a counterexample, but we find some new conformally invariant systems."
    }
